==============================================================================
THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE LICENSING & ATTRIBUTION
==============================================================================

SpectraStrike Hub utilizes several open-source third-party dependencies. Below is 
the licensing information for all core dependencies bundled or used by this project:

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Python Backend Dependencies (backend/requirements.txt)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* FastAPI (https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Web framework for building APIs.

* Uvicorn (https://github.com/encode/uvicorn)
  - License: BSD 3-Clause License
  - Description: ASGI web server implementation.

* mss (https://github.com/bobo383/python-mss)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Ultra-fast screen screenshot capturing utility.

* Pillow (https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow)
  - License: HPND License (Historical Permission Notice and Disclaimer)
  - Description: Friendly PIL fork for image processing.

* mcp (https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/python-sdk)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Model Context Protocol Python SDK.

* requests (https://github.com/psf/requests)
  - License: Apache License 2.0
  - Description: Elegant and simple HTTP library for Python.

* httpx (https://github.com/encode/httpx)
  - License: BSD 3-Clause License
  - Description: Next-generation HTTP client for Python.

* openrgb-python (https://github.com/jath03/openrgb-python)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Python client for the OpenRGB SDK server.

* winsdk (https://github.com/pywinrt/pywinrt)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Python bindings for the Windows Runtime (WinRT) APIs.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JavaScript Frontend Dependencies (frontend/package.json)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* React & React-DOM (https://github.com/facebook/react)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: JavaScript library for building user interfaces.

* Lucide React (https://github.com/lucide-icons/lucide)
  - License: ISC License
  - Description: Beautiful & consistent icon library.

* Vite (https://github.com/vitejs/vite)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Next-generation frontend tooling.

* ESLint (https://github.com/eslint/eslint)
  - License: MIT License
  - Description: Pluggable JavaScript linter.
